From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude.ai.2026@simonlaux.de>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 22:53:39 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 52/52] web-app: strip tracking params from links (open-side +
 paste chip + setting)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Links picked up from the web arrive carrying tracking cruft — utm_*
campaign tags, fbclid/gclid click ids, YouTube si=, Amazon aff refs. This
removes the known trackers automatically, with visibility instead of a
consent prompt: one setting, on by default.

- utils/trackingParams.ts: pure stripTrackingParams(url). Allowlist only,
  never "drop all query params" (t= on YouTube is a timestamp, v= the
  video). Global utm_*/click-ids, plus per-domain rules for youtube,
  instagram, x/twitter, spotify, tiktok and amazon (query params + trailing
  /ref= path segment, keeping th=). Raw query-string surgery keeps the
  untouched params byte-for-byte. Returns null when nothing changed or the
  input is not a parseable http(s) URL.
- hooks/useOpenLinkSafely.ts: the open side. Before runtime.openLink, swap
  in the cleaned URL when the setting is on. Silent, http(s) only; the
  non-http copy/confirm flow is untouched.
- setting stripTrackingLinks (shared-types + state, default true) with a
  plain-label DesktopSettingsSwitch in Chats and Media.

- Composer paste chip: tracking arrives via paste, and paste is the only
  safe moment to rewrite draft text. utils/trackingParams.ts grows a pure
  stripTrackingFromPaste(text): when the pasted plain text holds exactly one
  strippable http(s) URL it returns the rewritten text plus the url pair,
  and returns null on any doubt (no URL, nothing strippable, multiple URLs)
  so the paste falls through untouched. Composer.tsx's existing onPaste path
  (compose mode only — the edit input has no onPaste wired) intercepts the
  no-file plain-text branch when the setting is on, inserts the cleaned text
  via insertStringAtCursorPosition instead of the raw paste, and shows a
  quiet upper-bar chip ("Tracking removed from link") reusing the link-
  preview ghost's .bar styles, with Undo (swaps the cleaned URL back to the
  original in the draft) and dismiss. The chip is per-message: cleared on
  undo, dismiss, send, and chat switch.
- tests/trackingParams.test.ts: mocha/chai over the strip rules and the
  paste rewrite / single-URL fallback.
